On 07/28/2011 07:48 AM, Adam wrote:
&gt; Hi,
&gt;
&gt; An intranet site I am trying to crawl with the current Heritrix 3.1.0 snapshot offers 3 authentication types: NTLM, Digest, Basic in that order of priority. The crawler HTTP client fails to deal with NTLM which is fine but I&#39;d then expect it to try and negotiate with Digest and then Basic which doesn&#39;t happen. To work around this I had to set the AuthPolicy priority in the org.archive.modules.credential.HttpAuthenticationCredential populate() method as follows:
&gt;
&gt; List authPrefs = new ArrayList(2);
&gt; authPrefs.add(AuthPolicy.DIGEST);
&gt; authPrefs.add(AuthPolicy.BASIC);
&gt; http.getParams().setParameter(AuthPolicy.AUTH_SCHEME_PRIORITY, authPrefs)
&gt;
&gt; and then the HTTP client successfully negotiated the authentication.
&gt;
&gt; Adam
